During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki discussed the Biden-Harris administration's efforts to strengthen America's supply chains. Psaki highlighted the key findings from reviews conducted as part of President Biden's executive order on supply chains. The administration emphasized the need to build back better by leveraging American workers, diversity, small businesses, alliances, and imagination. The administration announced several immediate actions, including investments in advanced pharmaceutical manufacturing technologies, battery research and manufacturing, critical minerals and materials, and semiconductors. Psaki also mentioned the launch of a Supply Chain Disruptions Task Force to address near-term supply chain issues. In addition to supply chain security, Psaki discussed the administration's focus on infrastructure, voting rights, and reunifying families separated at the border.